President Trump sat down with Laura Ingraham for an interview where he discussed the Pittsburgh shooting, his love for the country, and the migrant caravan. The shooter in Pittsburgh disliked Trump because of his relationship with Israel. Trump emphasized that people should not let these incidents disrupt their lives. He described himself as a nationalist, stating that he loves the country and wants to take care of it. Trump also talked about the loopholes in immigration law that allow the asylum system to be exploited, mentioning plans to build tent cities where migrants can wait for their asylum hearings.